    "refcode_short": "AH 314.1",
    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 314.1 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "There should always be a fixed principle with Christian parents to be united in the government of their children. There is a fault in this respect with some parents&mdash;a lack of union. The fault is sometimes with the father, but oftener with the mother. The fond mother pets and indulges her children. The father&apos;s labor calls him from home often, and from the society of his children. The mother&apos;s influence tells. Her example does much toward forming the character of the children.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"1T 156.1\" data-link=\"116.795\">Testimonies for the Church 1:156</span>.</span></a></sup>",
