    "content": "<strong>Children Are Confused by Parents at Variance</strong>&mdash;The family firm must be well organized. Together the father and mother must consider their responsibilities, and with a clear comprehension undertake their task. There is to be no variance. The father and mother should never in the presence of their children criticize each other&apos;s plans and judgment.",
