    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Hearts to Be Bound by the Silken Cord of Love</strong> .&mdash;Father and mother, bind your hearts in closest, happiest union. Do not grow apart, but bind yourselves more closely to each other; then you are prepared to bind your children&apos;s hearts to you by the silken cord of love.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">13<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 9-15-1891\" data-link=\"821.11491\">The Review and Herald, September 15, 1891</span>.</span></a></sup>",
